90 pt rated Cookies & Cork Birthday Gift
List.Description:
Wine.com brings to you a unique tasting experience from Cookies & Corks - all natural, gourmet, sweet and savory cookies crafted to pair with wines. These decadent cookies contain distinctive ingredients like espresso, parmesan, thyme, dark chocolate, lemon, rosemary and sea salt - all perfect complements to wine varietals. We encourage you or your gift recipients to have fun pairing these cookies with two 90 point rated wines, the 94 point rated Penley Estates Phoenix Cabernet Sauvignon and the 90 point rated Nino Franco Rustico Prosecco. But no matter how you mix and match, a dynamic combination of flavors show up to entertain and delight you. Wine Gift Includes:
  • Penley Estate Phoenix Cabernet Sauvignon:
    The nose consists of violets, black currant leaf, ripe wild berry and integrated spice of the Cabernet grape. Mulberry and blackberry are the dominant fruit flavors enhanced by a tight palate with silky grape tannins and elegant complex cedar oak, so typical of Penley Style. A very generous mid palate with a hints of licorice and chocolate lingers on the finish.

  • Nino Franco Rustico Prosecco
    Nino Franco's non-vintage sparkling Rustico Prosecco is unquestionably the world's finest value in a high quality, Champagne look-alike. The non-vintage, light-bodied Prosecco di Valdobiaddene Rustico offers gorgeously elegant, fresh, lively fruit, notes of bread dough and citrus, and persistent effervescence.

  • Cookies & Corks Red Wine Pairing Box Contains fifteen bite-sized cookies, created to pair with different red wine varietals. Includes five Espresso Chocolate Peanut Butter, five White Cheddar Rosemary, and five Shortbread cookies.


  • Cookies & Corks Sparkling Wine Pairing BoxContains fifteen bite-sized cookies, created to pair with different sparkling wine varietals. Includes five Zesty Lemon, five Parmesan Thyme, and five Sea Salt Chocolate Oatmeal.

  • Greet Sheet Festive Birthday greet sheet




    Wine gift sets & baskets may be packaged with the bottles separately boxed for their protection during shipment

    Pursuant to state laws in New York, gifts that contain both food and wine will be sent in two separate packages.
